items.name: Futanarimix Large Futanari Erection LoCon
items.description:
Details

The provided file is epoch 30/44. There could be a better version but based on my limited testing, epoch 30/33/35 are the most consistent.

All training settings are visible within the file metadata.

This version shouldn't affect the style too much, but it will modify composition a lot.

Usage

Works best with models that contain NAI as this was trained on NAI.

Please use alabasterBlend_v10.safetensors [43381b29f9] or kotosmix_v10.safetensors [0f789fc3c4] or abyssfuta.safetensors [62b68f1181] or AbyssFluffyKemono.safetensors [1f5b74ae12] with DPM++ 2M Karras @ 20 steps minimum + 512 x 768.

If you really want more 2D style rather than 3D, add the following to the negative prompt:
(3D, realistic, render)

Changes

DAdaptAdam

Cosine with repeats (3)

Lower repeats, higher epochs

Increased training data from 253 images to 687 images

Added 2D images to the training data to prevent the style from changing too much.

Double the amount of 2D images compared to 3D images

items.name: Britomart (Fate) LoRA
items.description:
Britomart (Fate) LoRA

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

V2

This model was trained using 24 images of her. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models. The shape of her swimsuit is a bit random, might require a few gens to get it right.

Recommended weight is 0.9 to 1.

Trigger words is fgobritomart

Example images were generated using jafamix v4 with 30 steps, then hires. fixed by 1.5 with adetailer enabled for the faces.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

V1

This model was trained using 21 images of Britomart. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models.

I recommend to use a weight of around 0.7. It was mostly trained on her 4th ascension outfit, and around half of the images were nsfw, so be prepared to get nipples when generating.

Trigger word is Britomart, if you want to get the outfit more consisten add swimsuit, and if you want something closer to her 2nd ascension add white pants and elbow gloves.

Example images were generated using AOM2 hard with 20 steps, that were then upscaled on 0.2 denoising strength and 150 steps with a lower weight on the LoRA

I will upload a better model once more source material is available to train on

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Andalites (Animorphs Series) - Experimental
items.description:
I am the Reindeer Czar, I love Reindeer! I have wanted to make an Andalite model for a while now, so I started!

Now why does the Reindeer Czar want to make Andalites? Because as Marco called them in the book series, they are Blue Space Deer of course. :P

Good training data is limited here, so the idea is to use AI generated Andalites to make more training data, but that means lucky generations, or good in-painting.

So if you want to add some images to help refine this model, please go ahead!

The model is rough, but it has the right idea. Realistic models seem to do best. Anime models try and give them animal ears instead of stalk eyes, if you figure out how to make some good anime Andalites please share.

Animated models seem to like a weight of 0.9, and realistic models may do well at 1.0, it seems almost underbaked, even though it's 4000 steps. Maybe next time we can try more.

Positive helper tags are: (taur:1.6), tail blade, antennae, full body

Negative helper tags are: two tails, animal ears

This is experimental work in progress, so please, don't rate badly yet. ;)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

items.name: Species: Aslan | Traveller RPG
items.description:
This LoRA aids in generating images of Aslans from the Traveller RPG universe. It works for both realistic and illustrated styles.

Excerpt from the Traveller wiki:

The Aslan of Kusyu (Dark Nebula 1226) are a Major Race, of four-limbed, upright, bipedal, carnivore/pouncer, humanoid/felidoid stock.

Their name for themselves is the Fteirle and their large interstellar empire is known as the Aslan Hierate. The earliest Terran explorers saw in them a vague resemblance to the Terran lion, and they have been described (by Terrans) as lion-like ever since, although there is very little true similarity. The derivation of the word Aslan is contested.

They are the youngest of all the major sophonts, having had starflight for less than 3,200 standard years.

items.name: Comfyroll
items.description:
The Comfyroll models were built for use with ComfyUI, but also produce good results on Auto1111. They currently comprises of a merge of 4 checkpoints.

The models can produce colorful high contrast images in a variety of illustration styles. A pseudo-HDR look can be easily produced using the template workflows provided for the models.

These checkpoint merges are particuarly good for:

  • semi-realistic styles (use Comyroll)

  • stylized anime (use ComyrollAnime)

  • illustration styles

  • 2D, 2.5D

  • NSFW

These merges were not designed for creating NSFW and in general do not produce unsafe images unless you deliberately prompt for them.

Comfyroll workflow templates:

A collection of workflow templates has been designed for use with these models. The collection includes workflows for anime and illustration styles.

https://civitai.com/models/59806/comfyroll-template-workflows

These templates were used to create the sample illustrations for the models. I have indicated in the comments on each image the template that was used and additional information such as the clip skip, noise masks and lora.

It is also planned to create example prompts for use in Auto1111.

Recommended settings (Comfy):

Sampler: dpmpp_2m karras, uni_pc normal

Steps: 10 steps for a contrasty manga-style look and 30+ steps for a smoother look

Clip Skip: both -1 and -2 both work well, -2 provides a good semi-realistic look, -1 is great for anime and illustration styles

Img2Img Denoise: usually between 0.85 to 0.95 (lower values are good for illustration styles)

VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (the models do not currently have baked VAE, so you will need a VAE loader node in your workflows)

These models work best when combined with noise masks in Img2Img or ControlNet. Please see the Comfyroll Template Workflows for examples of how to use noise. Recommended noise patterns include white noise, pink noise, dissolve noise and perlin noise.

Recommended settings (Auto 1111):

Hires fix is strongly recommended

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, UniPC,

Steps: 20, Hires 30

Clip Skip: -2

VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

Prompting:

Here are some suggested keywords to use in prompts for these models:

  • Semi-Realistic Style

    • 2.5D, semi-realistic,

    • highest quality, detailed,

    • depth of field, natural blur, bokeh, HDR,

  • Anime Style (ComfyrollAnime)

    • 2D, 2.5D,

    • anime line-art, illustration,

  • Illustration Styles

    • 2D, 2.5D,

    • detailed concept drawing, illustration, line-art, stylized,

  • Lighting

    • subsurface scattering, chromatic lighting,

    • neon lighting, moody lighting, cinematic lighting,

  • Color

    • colorized, flat colors, limited color palette

  • Camera

    • from-above, from-below, from-side, from-behind,

    • portrait, cowboy-shot, close-up, long-shot,

Recommended LoRAs:

ukiyo-e 30% strength

NijiV5style with ComfyrollAnime, 50% strength

Longan/竜眼 Style with ComfyrollAnime, 70% strength

Textual inversions:

https://upscale.wiki/wiki/Model_Database

items.name: Brandon Woelfel Style
items.description:
Brandon Woelfel is an American photographer known for his distinctive style characterized by dreamy, atmospheric, and whimsical images. He has gained a significant following on social media platforms, where he shares his creative and visually captivating photographs.

Woelfel's photography often features vibrant colors, bokeh effects, and play with light, creating a magical and ethereal ambiance. He frequently incorporates fairy lights, reflective surfaces, and unique light sources to enhance the mood and add a touch of fantasy to his images.

His portraits showcase a mix of fashion, lifestyle, and personal expression, capturing the beauty and individuality of his subjects. Woelfel has a talent for creating an intimate connection with his models, bringing out their personalities and emotions in his photographs.

In addition to his portraiture work, Woelfel also captures stunning cityscapes, landscapes, and night scenes. His images have a romantic and nostalgic quality that resonates with viewers, often evoking a sense of wonder and a yearning for adventure.

Woelfel's popularity on social media has allowed him to collaborate with various brands and influencers, further expanding his reach and creative opportunities. He has also published a book, " Luminescence," featuring a collection of his photographs.

Brandon Woelfel's photography stands out for its enchanting aesthetic, skillful use of lighting, and ability to create a sense of escapism and wonder. His images capture moments of beauty and evoke emotions, drawing viewers into his magical world of light and color.

items.name: ChillyMix
items.description:
This is another attempt to make a free/open version of the ChilloutMix.

If you like my work, feel free to buy me a coffee at ko-fi. https://ko-fi.com/mixboy

There are chilled_re_generic v1/v2 and chilled_remix, but they are not good enough to generate the desired results.

Merged models are the following: (all models are merged with the SuperMerger extension)

  • V2 version only: use the chillyMixBase - include pyro's_pov models (results NSFW fix)

  • analogDiffusion_10 (Fp16)

  • F222 (Fp32) see also F222 at https://rentry.co/sdmodels

  • r34_e4 (Fp16) - from https://rentry.co/sdmodels

  • neverendingDreamNED_noVae (Fp32) by @Lykon

  • muse_v1 (Fp32) by @9muses_arts

Merge Recipe

The following three steps are modified recipe based on https://rentry.org/hdgrecipes#instructions_1 (use the Analog Diffusion model instead of the Novel AI model)

(This recipe is for the V1 version. V2 recipe uses the chillyMixBase )

  • analogDiffusion_10 x 0.95 + v1-5-pruned-emaonly x 0.05 -> MERGE1 (fp16)

  • MERGE1 + (f222-Fp16 - v1-5-pruned-emaonly) x 1 : Add difference -> MERGE2 (fp16)

  • MERGE2 x 0.75 + r34_e4-Fp16 x 0.25 -> MIX_BASE (fp16)

These three models are used by PoV Skin Texture - r34 Lucid Black (it is used by the ChilloutMix as described it's description.)

In this recipe, you can get the MIX_BASE but it is not good to use it alone. It sometimes produces overfitted results. but simply merge with a good model like the NED to fix this issue. and it could maintain some chilloutmix's own property.)

add the NED(NeverEndingDream - NO VAE version) to the MIX_BASE:

(for V2 recipe case, MIX_BASE == chillyMixBase)

  • MIX_GOOD = MIX_BASE x 0.25 + neverendingDreamNED_noVae x 0.75 (fp16)

Finally, mix the Muse V1-fixed (fixed by the model toolkit extension) for a realistic model. (Muse v1 seems very similar to the ChilloutMix.)

MIX_GOOD + museV1_v1-fixed are merged with the SuperMerger with the following settings:

MIX_GOOD x (1-alpha) + museV1_v1-prunedFp16-fixed x alpha (0.0,1.0,0.925925925925926,0.740740740740741,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.740740740740741,0.925925925925926,1.0,0.925925925925926,0.740740740740741,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.7,0.740740740740741,0.925925925925926,1.0)

Selected alpha MBW(Merge Block Weights) are modified R_SMOOTHSTEP/4

(MBWs are selected for more realistic and ChilloutMix like. I'm not sure that MBWs are optimal but it seems best for my use cases.)

Recommends

  • All posted images use "DDetailer script extension" or "After Detailer" for beautiful faces.

  • DPM++ 2M Karras sampling method.

  • "EasyNegative" "negative_hand-neg", "ng_deepnegative_v1_75t" embeddings are recommended in the negative prompt.

    • "badhandv4" have anime contamination at a higher weight ratio.

    • use "badhandv4" with a normal weight ratio or use the "bad-hand-5" alternative.

  • Set Clip skip: 2, ENSD: 31337

Useful AUTOMATIC1111's webui extensions

  • SuperMerger extension

  • Lora Block Weight extension

  • webui model toolkit to examine Loras and models.

  • civitai extension to add several useful features for civitai.

ChangeLog

  • 2023/05/29 : V2 version preview - use the chillyMixBase: it includes pyro's pov checkpoint and results in NSFW enhancement and more cleaner skin.

  • 2023/06/22: VAE baked version added

  • 2023/06/23: inpainting version added for inpainting.

License

All used models here have "Have different permissions when sharing merges" license permission, so I do not try to add any restriction on it.

CreativeML-Open Rail-M

This model permits users to:

✔Use the model without crediting the creator

✔Sell images they generate

✔Run on services that generate images for money

✔Share merges using this model

✔Sell this model or merges using this model

✔Have different permissions when sharing merges

Support me

If you like my work, feel free to buy me a coffee at ko-fi. https://ko-fi.com/mixboy

items.name: Dark dungeon
items.description:
This is a simple LoRA aimed at generating dungeon backgrounds. I know some base models are able to do it, but they do it inconsistently and not with the more underground / dark look I was going for. See example images for comparison with base model.

Use weight 1.0 or more. Trigger word: dungeon. I recommend prompting other tags to help describe what you want to generate. You can be creative, but here's a few suggestions: candle, torch, fire, dark, darkness, backlighting, shadow, stairs, hallway, room, cell, etc. Use different aspect ratios and describe the composition and character placement.

You can use other loras, for characters, style, concepts, etc. The dataset included scenery images but also some anime NSFW images. See my posts in the gallery.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

Anyway. trigger is SFGuile. Other trigger words: green tanktop, necklace, camouflage pants, flag tattoo, boots. You have more chance of getting the tattoo right with hires fix.

Well, I hope you enjoy this model more than I did :P

items.name: Alyssa Hart
items.description:
📝Biography📝

(generation advice below) 👇

🌟Alyssa Hart 🌟

is an American model and social media personality originally from Boston, Massachusetts. Born on October 15, 1989, the Libra is currently 32 years young. Standing at 5 feet 4 inches tall, Alyssa has a charming smile and maintains an active lifestyle to keep her 114 pound figure in shape.

When she's not promoting brands or connecting with her over 20,000 Twitter followers, Alyssa enjoys traveling, shopping, and furthering her modeling career. Though Alyssa prefers to keep details of her personal life private, she has appeared in various short films and built up an impressive modeling portfolio over the years. Having accumulated over half a million dollars through her successful endeavors, the sky is the limit for this hardworking content creator. Alyssa serves as an inspiration for those looking to follow their dreams in today's digital world.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling (Using auto1111 or similar UX) 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ 1.

  • Samples done with CyberRealistic v2.1 with sampling steps generally between 40 to 80 using Euler a, DPM++ 2M Karras and UniPC.

  • When testing a prompt, I often do a low lowres gen of multiple images, then choose the seed I like and upscale.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Portrait and close-ups work great using Hires. fix and 8X NMKD-Faces at 0.15 - 0.45 denoise strength.

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two, but often just the Hires. fix is good enough to capture enough details for the subject matter.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • The prompts continue to evolve. CyberRealistic is a reasonably flexible model for being realism focused and still capturing abstract concepts. I still think they have trumped the SD 1.5 game. 👑

  • Feedback appreciated. Please leave a review if you've used this LORA. 👍

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

This is a LoRA trained on AI generated pictures using the prompt "marker art" (made using the Bing Image Creator). My models are not trained to achieve the exact style of their source, but to change the general vibe of the image.
